      </div>
      <h1 class='title'>Housing (Stock Transfer)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 cc270-1WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_270ws' title='Col. 270WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c270WS' name='column_270ws' href='#column_270ws' rel='bookmark'>270WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06342'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_320'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-drew' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_320' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Drew' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-drew" title="Mr David Drew">Mr. Drew</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06342">To ask the Deputy Prime Minister if he will list housing allocations created as a result of stock transfer from a local authority which have since been transferred to another housing association. [88322]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06343'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_321'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-tony-mcnulty' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_321' title='Link to this speech by Mr Tony McNulty' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-tony-mcnulty" title="Mr Tony McNulty">Mr. McNulty</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06343">None of the housing associations created to receive stock transferred from a local authority have since transferred the stock onto another housing association. Some of these associations have undergone a name change or have become a subsidiary of a group structure, but they have remained separate legal entities with individual boards.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06344'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_322'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-drew' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_322' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Drew' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-drew" title="Mr David Drew">Mr. Drew</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06344">To ask the Deputy Prime Minister what<span class="italic">(a)</span> the level of homelessness and <span class="italic">(b)</span> housing list numbers for those requiring housing were in each authority which has undergone stock transfer (i) at the time of transfer and (ii) at each year-end subsequent to unit transfers. [88323]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06345'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_323'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mrs-barbara-roche' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_323' title='Link to this speech by Mrs Barbara Roche' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mrs-barbara-roche" title="Mrs Barbara Roche">Mrs. Roche</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06345">A comprehensive table presenting available information since 1988/99 in respect of homelessness household accepted annually, those accommodated at 31 March, and total households on the housing register at 1 April deemed to be "in need" has been placed in the Library of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06346'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_324'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-drew' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_324' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Drew' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-drew" title="Mr David Drew">Mr. Drew</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06346">To ask the Deputy Prime Minister what steps he has taken to ensure that there is no conflict of interest in the position of senior local authority officers promoting stock transfer. [88324]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06347'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_325'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-tony-mcnulty' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_325' title='Link to this speech by Mr Tony McNulty' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-tony-mcnulty" title="Mr Tony McNulty">Mr. McNulty</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06347">The current Housing Transfer Guidance includes detailed advice on how to deal with potential conflicts of interest when senior local authority officers are involved in a proposed housing
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_271ws' title='Col. 271WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c271WS' name='column_271ws' href='#column_271ws' rel='bookmark'>271WS</a>
          transfer. Specific advice is addressed to those officers proposing to move to the prospective new landlord. This advice also covers consultants advising the authority and the prospective new landlord over various aspects of the transfer.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
